<title>USA: Geoworks sees lower than forecast Q4 sales.</title>
<headline>Geoworks sees lower than forecast Q4 sales.</headline>
<dateline>ALAMEDA, Calif. 1997-03-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Geoworks said Thursday it expects to report fourth quarter revenues of between $1.8 million and $2.2 million, which is lower than earlier anticipated.</p>
<p>The company said the shortfall results from delays in recognition of non-recurring engineering fees and the adoption of a more conservative approach to estimating product revenues. Under the new approach, Geoworks said it is focusing estimates on product sell-through to the ultimate customer.</p>
<p>Geoworks makes software and mobile communicating devices for the cellular industry.</p>
